ly]]\n|-\n| [[W (UK TV channel)|W]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2| Vietnam || [[STAR World]] || || Upcoming\n|-\n| [[Vietnam Television|VTV6]] (''Junior version'') || Dubbed in Vietnamese || Yes\n|-\n|}\n\n==Print publications==\n===''Official MasterChef Cookbook Volume 1''===\nThe ''Official MasterChef Cookbook Volume 1'' was published by Random House Australia in December 2009. It contains recipes from the series 1 Top 20 contestants and top Australian and international chefs: Martin Boetz, Donovan Cooke, [[Pete Evans]], [[Manu Feildel]], [[Guy Grossi]], Alex Herbert, Matt Moran and Andrew Honeysett, [[Ben O'Donoghue]], [[Adrian Richardson]], Frank Shek, Emmanuel Stroobant and [[Adriano Zumbo]]. There are also behind-the-scenes stories and culinary tips and tricks.\n\n===''MasterChef Magazine''===\n''MasterChef Magazine'', a monthly spin-off publication adopting the series' brand, went on sale in May 2010. Following a high-profile launch, the magazine exceeded its initial sales target within a short period of time, selling 90,000 copies in three days.<ref name=\"masterchefmag\">{{Cite news\n  | title = MasterChef magazine debut a sellout\n  | work=The Spy Report\n  | publisher=Media Spy\n  | date = 17 May 2010\n  | url = http://www.mediaspy.org/report/2010/05/17/masterchef-magazine-debut-a-sellout/\n  | accessdate =18 May 2010\n}}</ref> The magazine was published by News Magazines, a subsidiary of [[News Limited]].<ref name=\"masterchefmag2\">{{Cite news\n  | title = MasterChef Magazine arriving next week\n  | work=The Spy Report\n  | publisher=Media Spy\n  | date = 3 May 2010\n  | url = http://www.mediaspy.org/report/2010/05/03/masterchef-magazine-arriving-next-week/\n  | accessdate =18 May 2010\n}}</ref>\nAfter losing a third of its readers in one year, the magazine was closed in October 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mumbrella.com.au/newslifemedia-closes-masterchef-magazine-121380|title=NewsLifeMedia closes MasterChef Magazine \u2013 Mumbrella|date=12 October 2012|work=mumbrella.com.au|accessdate=25 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Television|Australia}}\n*[[MasterChef Australia contestants with television series]]\n*[[List of Australian television series]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.masterchef.com.au/home.htm ''MasterChef Australia''] \u2013 ''Official MasterChef Australia Website''\n*[http://ten.com.au/ ''Official Channel 10 Website''] \u2013 ''Official Network Ten Website (with free MasterChef episodes)''\n*[https://www.endemolshine.com.au/#/masterchef/ ''Official Production Website''] \u2013 ''Official Shine Australia Production Website''\n*{{IMDb title|1433870}}\n*{{tv.com show|masterchef-australia}}\n*{{Twitter}}\n\n{{MasterChef}}\n{{MasterChef Australia}}\n{{AACTA Award Best Reality Television Series}}\n{{Network Ten programming}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Masterchef Australia}}\n[[Category:Network 10 shows]]\n[[Category:2009 Australian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000s Australian television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Australian television series]]\n[[Category:Australian cooking television series]]\n[[Category:MasterChef Australia| ]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Sydney]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Melbourne]]\n[[Category:Television series by Fremantle (company)]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Cooking competitions in Australia]]\n[[Category:Australian television series based on British television series]]\n", "name_user": "Pra0022", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHosts and judges", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MasterChef_Australia"}
{"title_page": "Barwan Kala, Bihar", "text_new": "'''Barwan Kala''' is a village located in the \u201c''Tehsil Adhaura''\u201d of \u201cKaimur District of the state of [[Bihar]] in [[India]]. It is a rural [[village]] taking place in the list with other 128 villages. It is said that [[bachelors]] in this village has not seen a single [[marriage]] in the last 50 years, it means Barwan Kala in Bihar is witnessing singledom.<ref>{{cite web |title=8 Unique Indian Villages That&#039;ll Surprise You - GoodTimes: Lifestyle, Food, Travel, Fashion, Weddings, Bollywood, Tech, Videos &amp; Photos |url=https://www.mygoodtimes.in/travel/bizarre-destinations/8-unique-indian-villages-thatll-surprise-you/ |website=mygoodtimes.in}}</ref>\n\n==Present State==\nIt falls under the Assembly Constituency of \u201cChainpur\u201d & Loksabha Constituency of \u201cSasaram\u201d.\n\n==Population==\nAs per the Census of 2011 by Government of India, total 244 families were residing. The population was 1387 of which 743 are males while 644 are females.\n\n==Demographic Information==\nThe [[Pincode]] of Barwan Kala is 821102 with [[post office]] Adhaura. Its dialing code is 06180.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pincode of BARWAN KALAN, Bihar is 821102 |url=https://pincodes.info/in/Bihar/Kaimur-Bhabua/Jaitpur-Kalan/BARWAN-KALAN/ |website=pincodes.info}}</ref>\n==In Limelight==\nThe village has somewhere around 130 bachelors. It is estimated that it is the highest number of unmarried males in any village of Bihar. The reason behind this is the poor condition of village. They feel no outsider would give the hand of their daughters to the village youth which is disconnected from the rest of the world in terms of no telecommunication, irrigation, power & water.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bihar 'bachelor villages' carve road through mountains, to make way for brides |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india/bihar-bachelor-villages-carve-road-through-mountains-to-make-way-for-brides/story-20OkMFgcRslW1c9MkdDlBO.html |website=hindustantimes.com}}</ref>\n\n==Transportation==\nAt present, there is no railway station near to this village. One has to reach Bhabua via road to reach here.\n==School==\nThe village has a +2 high school located in Adhaura block. It is a co-ed school for class 1st till Class 12th.<ref>{{cite web |title=UPGRADED +2 HIGH  SCHOOL BARWAN KALA  - Barwan Kala, District Kaimur (bhabua) (Bihar) |url=https://schools.org.in/kaimur-(bhabua)/10310304201/upgraded-+2-high-school-barwan-kala.html |website=schools.org.in}}</ref>\n==References==\n", "text_old": "'''Barwan Kala''' is a village located in the \u201c''Tehsil Adhaura''\u201d of \u201cKaimur District of the state of [[Bihar]] in [[India]]. It is a rural [[village]] taking place in the list with other 128 villages. It is said that [[bachelors]] in this village has not seen a single [[marriage]] in the last 50 years, it means Barwan Kala in Bihar is witnessing singledom.<ref>{{cite web |title=8 Unique Indian Villages That&#039;ll Surprise You - GoodTimes: Lifestyle, Food, Travel, Fashion, Weddings, Bollywood, Tech, Videos &amp; Photos |url=https://www.mygoodtimes.in/travel/bizarre-destinations/8-unique-indian-villages-thatll-surprise-you/ |website=mygoodtimes.in}}</ref>\n\n==Present State==\nIt falls under the Assembly Constituency of \u201cChainpur\u201d & Loksabha Constituency of \u201cSasaram\u201d.\n\n==Population==\nAs per the Census of 2011 by Government of India, total 244 families were residing. The population was 1387 of which 743 are males while 644 are females.\n\n==Demographic Information==\nThe [[Pincode]] of Barwan Kala is 821102 with [[post office]] Adhaura. Its dialing code is 06180.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pincode of BARWAN KALAN, Bihar is 821102 |url=https://pincodes.info/in/Bihar/Kaimur-Bhabua/Jaitpur-Kalan/BARWAN-KALAN/ |website=pincodes.info}}</ref>\n==In Limelight==\nThe village has somewhere around 130 bachelors. It is estimated that it is the highest number of unmarried males in any village of Bihar. The reason behind this is the poor condition of village. They feel no outsider would give the hand of their daughters to the village youth which is disconnected from the rest of the world in terms of no telecommunication, irrigation, power & water.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bihar 'bachelor villages' carve road through mountains, to make way for brides |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india/bihar-bachelor-villages-carve-road-through-mountains-to-make-way-for-brides/story-20OkMFgcRslW1c9MkdDlBO.html |website=hindustantimes.com}}</ref>\n\n==Transportation==\nAt present, there is no railway station near to this village. One has to reach Bhabua via road to reach here.\n==School==\nThe village has a +2 high school located in Adhaura block. It is a co-ed school for class 1st till Class 12th.\n==References==\n", "name_user": "Rajeev Gaur123", "label": "safe", "comment": "References updation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barwan_Kala,_Bihar"}
{"title_page": "Life Time Fitness", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|Life Fitness}}\n{{External links|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Life Time, Inc.\n| logo = Life Time Fitness logo.svg\n| logo_size = \n| logo_alt = \n| logo_caption = \n| logo_padding = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| image_caption = \n| native_name = \n| former_name = FCA ltd.\n| type = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| industry = \n| founded = {{start date and age|1990}} (as FCA, Ltd.)<br>{{start date and age|1992}} (as Life Time Fitness, Inc.)\n| founder = Bahram Akradi\n| hq_location = [[Chanhassen, Minnesota]], U.S.\n| hq_location_city = \n| hq_location_country = \n| area_served = United States and [[Canada]]\n| key_people = Bahram Akradi, <br>Founder/Chairman/CEO\n| num_employees = 36,000\n| products = \n| brands = \n| services = \n| owner = [[Leonard Green & Partners]]<br>[[TPG Capital]]\n| website = {{URL|lifetime.life}}\n}}\n'''Life Time, Inc.''' is a chain of [[health club]]s in the [[United States]] and [[Canada]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Life Time Athletic - Fitness Center in Chanhassen, Minnesota.jpg|thumb|260px|Life Time Athletic, [[Chanhassen, Minnesota]]]]\n[[File:Life Time Fitness, Alpharetta, GA Oct 2017.jpg|thumb|260px|Life Time Inc. facility, [[Alpharetta, Georgia]]]]\nThe company was founded by chairman and [[chief executive officer]], Bahram Akradi.<ref>{{cite web|title=Who's Who in Fitness |url=http://preview.fitnessbusiness-pro.com/mag/fitness_whos_fitness/ |publisher=fitnessbusiness-pro.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120923004340/http://preview.fitnessbusiness-pro.com/mag/fitness_whos_fitness/ |archivedate=2012-09-23 }}</ref> The company was incorporated in 1990 as FCA, Ltd., a Minnesota corporation, and registered the name Life Time Fitness in 1992.<ref>{{cite web|title=Twin Cities health clubs go national|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/twincities/stories/1998/12/07/daily17.html|publisher=bizjournals.com/twincities/}}</ref> The first club opened in [[Brooklyn Park, Minnesota]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Fact Sheet|url=http://www.lifetimefitness.com/aboutlifetime/company/index.cfm?strWebAction=fact_sheet|publisher=lifetimefitness.com/aboutlifetime/company|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120724180828/http://www.lifetimefitness.com/aboutlifetime/company/index.cfm?strWebAction=fact_sheet|archivedate=2012-07-24}}</ref> Several locations were added to the [[Minneapolis\u2013St. Paul]] area before the chain expanded to suburban communities in other states. Most Life Time Fitness centers are located in [[exurban]] or fringe [[suburban]] areas in medium to large-sized metropolitan areas, with some locations in central city or inner suburban areas. The oldest facility is in [[Eagan, Minnesota|Eagan]], [[Minnesota]]. In 2017 they announced plans for a new facility inside of the [[Southdale Center|Southdale Mall]] in [[Edina, Minnesota]], replacing the former tenant [[J. C. Penney|J.C. Penney]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.startribune.com/miss-penney-s-already-see-southdale-at-60-exhibit-closing-aug-31/427011231/|title=Miss Penney's already? See \"Southdale at 60\" exhibit, closing Aug. 31|work=Star Tribune|access-date=2017-06-07}}</ref> \n\nClubs in more populated affluent metropolitan areas fall under the \"Life Time Athletic\" name while others in smaller metropolitan regions are known as \"Life Time Fitness\" clubs.[https://www.lifetime.life/view-all-locations.html]\n\nIn addition to its health clubs, the company has created or acquired, as of 2012, more than 200 annual races in the United States. These include the [[Life Time Tri Series]], the [[Leadville Race Series]], the Chequamegon Fat Tire Festival in [[Hayward, Wisconsin]],<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Pearson |first=Stephanie |date=September 2012 |title=Meet the New Boss |url=https://www.outsideonline.com/1903541/ultra-racings-new-boss |magazine=Outside |pages=26\u201328}}</ref>  the [[Dirty Kanza]] gravel bicycle race, and the [[Miami Marathon]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mylt.life/athletic-events.html?_ga=2.31059775.1865898324.1548301011-884867696.1548301011 |title=Athletic Events |website=Life Time |access-date=2019-01-23}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2014, Life Time Fitness, a publicly traded company, considered becoming a [[Real Estate Investment Trust]] (REIT) in response to pressure  from its largest shareholder, Marcato Capital Management. In March 2015, Life Time was acquired by private equity firms [[TPG Capital]] and [[Leonard Green & Partners]] in a [[leveraged buyout]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Tan|first=Gillian|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/leonard-green-tpg-to-take-life-time-fitness-private-1426508265|title=Leonard Green, TPG to Take Life Time Fitness Private|date=March 16, 2015|accessdate=March 16, 2015|publisher=wsj.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Waite|first=Kirstin|url=http://www.triathlonbusiness.com/2015/industry-news/life-time-fitness-sold-to-private-equity-firms-in-deal-valued-at-more-than-us4-billion/|title=Life Time Fitness sold to private equity firms in deal valued at more than US$4 billion|date=March 16, 2015|accessdate=March 16, 2015|publisher=triathlonbusiness.com}}</ref>\n\n==Lawsuit==\nSeveral employees of Life Time Fitness took the firm to court for withholding wages in 2004.<ref name=tws2T18>{{cite news\n |author= Mark Tabakman\n |title= Salary Deductions Can Make Workers Lose Exempt Status\n |work= Wage & Hour\n |quote= ... For example, in Baden-Winterwood v. Life Time Fitness Inc., the Sixth Circuit Court of Appeals held that deductions made by a health and fitness center employer from the base salaries of department heads to recoup portions of paid bonuses when the employees\u2019 performance fell below a certain prescribed level caused the workers to lose their exempt status under the Fair Labor Standards Act. ...\n |date=  June 8, 2009\n |url= http://wagehourlaw.foxrothschild.com/2009/06/articles/exemptions/salary-deductions-can-make-workers-lose-exempt-status/\n |accessdate= 2012-08-20\n}}</ref> In 2009, a court ruled in favor of employees in the case of ''Baden-Winterwood v. Life Time Fitness Inc.'', with a judgment that employees must be paid in accordance with federal and state wage-and-hour laws which require overtime pay for hours worked in excess of 40 in a workweek.<ref name=tws2T17>{{cite news\n |author=  Griffing, Marjorie\n |title= Not making the case for recovering overpayments from exempt employees.\n |work= Payroll Manager's Report\n |quote= Employees must be paid in accordance with federal and state wage-and-hour-laws, including laws requiring overtime pay for hours worked in excess of 40 in a workweek ... Baden-Winterwood et al. v. Life Time Fitness Inc. ...\n |date=  November 1, 2009\n |url= http://business.highbeam.com/2245/article-1G1-209697107/not-making-case-recovering-overpayments-exempt-employees\n |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140824013715/http://business.highbeam.com/2245/article-1G1-209697107/not-making-case-recovering-overpayments-exempt-employees\n |url-status= dead\n |archive-date= August 24, 2014\n |accessdate= 2012-08-20\n}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Northwest Athletic Clubs]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://lifetime.life Life Time Website]\n*[https://https://topshealthinfo.com/lifetime-fitness-membership-prices-locations. Life Time Fitness Membership, Prices, locations.Full Detail]\n\n{{Minnesota Corporations}}\n\n[[Category:Companies formerly listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Minnesota]]\n[[Category:Health clubs in the United States]]\n[[Category:2015 mergers and acquisitions]]\n[[Category:Private equity portfolio companies]]\n[[Category:Medical and health organizations based in Minnesota]]\n[[Category:Chanhassen, Minnesota]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Life Fitness}}\n{{External links|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Life Time, Inc.\n| logo = Life Time Fitness logo.svg\n| logo_size = \n| logo_alt = \n| logo_caption = \n| logo_padding = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| image_caption = \n| native_name = \n| former_name = FCA ltd.\n| type = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| industry = \n| founded = {{start date and age|1990}} (as FCA, Ltd.)<br>{{start date and age|1992}} (as Life Time Fitness, Inc.)\n| founder = Bahram Akradi\n| hq_location = [[Chanhassen, Minnesota]], U.S.\n| hq_location_city = \n| hq_location_country = \n| area_served = United States and [[Canada]]\n| key_people = Bahram Akradi, <br>Founder/Chairman/CEO\n| num_employees = 36,000\n| products = \n| brands = \n| services = \n| owner = [[Leonard Green & Partners]]<br>[[TPG Capital]]\n| website = {{URL|lifetime.life}}\n}}\n'''Life Time, Inc.''' is a chain of [[health club]]s in the [[United States]] and [[Canada]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Life Time Athletic - Fitness Center in Chanhassen, Minnesota.jpg|thumb|260px|Life Time Athletic, [[Chanhassen, Minnesota]]]]\n[[File:Life Time Fitness, Alpharetta, GA Oct 2017.jpg|thumb|260px|Life Time Inc. facility, [[Alpharetta, Georgia]]]]\nThe company was founded by chairman and [[chief executive officer]], Bahram Akradi.<ref>{{cite web|title=Who's Who in Fitness |url=http://preview.fitnessbusiness-pro.com/mag/fitness_whos_fitness/ |publisher=fitnessbusiness-pro.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120923004340/http://preview.fitnessbusiness-pro.com/mag/fitness_whos_fitness/ |archivedate=2012-09-23 }}</ref> The company was incorporated in 1990 as FCA, Ltd., a Minnesota corporation, and registered the name Life Time Fitness in 1992.<ref>{{cite web|title=Twin Cities health clubs go national|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/twincities/stories/1998/12/07/daily17.html|publisher=bizjournals.com/twincities/}}</ref> The first club opened in [[Brooklyn Park, Minnesota]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Fact Sheet|url=http://www.lifetimefitness.com/aboutlifetime/company/index.cfm?strWebAction=fact_sheet|publisher=lifetimefitness.com/aboutlifetime/company|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120724180828/http://www.lifetimefitness.com/aboutlifetime/company/index.cfm?strWebAction=fact_sheet|archivedate=2012-07-24}}</ref> Several locations were added to the [[Minneapolis\u2013St. Paul]] area before the chain expanded to suburban communities in other states. Most Life Time Fitness centers are located in [[exurban]] or fringe [[suburban]] areas in medium to large-sized metropolitan areas, with some locations in central city or inner suburban areas. The oldest facility is in [[Eagan, Minnesota|Eagan]], [[Minnesota]]. In 2017 they announced plans for a new facility inside of the [[Southdale Center|Southdale Mall]] in [[Edina, Minnesota]], replacing the former tenant [[J. C. Penney|J.C. Penney]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.startribune.com/miss-penney-s-already-see-southdale-at-60-exhibit-closing-aug-31/427011231/|title=Miss Penney's already? See \"Southdale at 60\" exhibit, closing Aug. 31|work=Star Tribune|access-date=2017-06-07}}</ref> \n\nClubs in more populated affluent metropolitan areas fall under the \"Life Time Athletic\" name while others in smaller metropolitan regions are known as \"Life Time Fitness\" clubs.[https://www.lifetime.life/view-all-locations.html]\n\nIn addition to its health clubs, the company has created or acquired, as of 2012, more than 200 annual races in the United States. These include the [[Life Time Tri Series]], the [[Leadville Race Series]], the Chequamegon Fat Tire Festival in [[Hayward, Wisconsin]],<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Pearson |first=Stephanie |date=September 2012 |title=Meet the New Boss |url=https://www.outsideonline.com/1903541/ultra-racings-new-boss |magazine=Outside |pages=26\u201328}}</ref>  the [[Dirty Kanza]] gravel bicycle race, and the [[Miami Marathon]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mylt.life/athletic-events.html?_ga=2.31059775.1865898324.1548301011-884867696.1548301011 |title=Athletic Events |website=Life Time |access-date=2019-01-23}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2014, Life Time Fitness, a publicly traded company, considered becoming a [[Real Estate Investment Trust]] (REIT) in response to pressure  from its largest shareholder, Marcato Capital Management. In March 2015, Life Time was acquired by private equity firms [[TPG Capital]] and [[Leonard Green & Partners]] in a [[leveraged buyout]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Tan|first=Gillian|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/leonard-green-tpg-to-take-life-time-fitness-private-1426508265|title=Leonard Green, TPG to Take Life Time Fitness Private|date=March 16, 2015|accessdate=March 16, 2015|publisher=wsj.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Waite|first=Kirstin|url=http://www.triathlonbusiness.com/2015/industry-news/life-time-fitness-sold-to-private-equity-firms-in-deal-valued-at-more-than-us4-billion/|title=Life Time Fitness sold to private equity firms in deal valued at more than US$4 billion|date=March 16, 2015|accessdate=March 16, 2015|publisher=triathlonbusiness.com}}</ref>\n\n==Lawsuit==\nSeveral employees of Life Time Fitness took the firm to court for withholding wages in 2004.<ref name=tws2T18>{{cite news\n |author= Mark Tabakman\n |title= Salary Deductions Can Make Workers Lose Exempt Status\n |work= Wage & Hour\n |quote= ... For example, in Baden-Winterwood v. Life Time Fitness Inc., the Sixth Circuit Court of Appeals held that deductions made by a health and fitness center employer from the base salaries of department heads to recoup portions of paid bonuses when the employees\u2019 performance fell below a certain prescribed level caused the workers to lose their exempt status under the Fair Labor Standards Act. ...\n |date=  June 8, 2009\n |url= http://wagehourlaw.foxrothschild.com/2009/06/articles/exemptions/salary-deductions-can-make-workers-lose-exempt-status/\n |accessdate= 2012-08-20\n}}</ref> In 2009, a court ruled in favor of employees in the case of ''Baden-Winterwood v. Life Time Fitness Inc.'', with a judgment that employees must be paid in accordance with federal and state wage-and-hour laws which require overtime pay for hours worked in excess of 40 in a workweek.<ref name=tws2T17>{{cite news\n |author=  Griffing, Marjorie\n |title= Not making the case for recovering overpayments from exempt employees.\n |work= Payroll Manager's Report\n |quote= Employees must be paid in accordance with federal and state wage-and-hour-laws, including laws requiring overtime pay for hours worked in excess of 40 in a workweek ... Baden-Winterwood et al. v. Life Time Fitness Inc. ...\n |date=  November 1, 2009\n |url= http://business.highbeam.com/2245/article-1G1-209697107/not-making-case-recovering-overpayments-exempt-employees\n |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140824013715/http://business.highbeam.com/2245/article-1G1-209697107/not-making-case-recovering-overpayments-exempt-employees\n |url-status= dead\n |archive-date= August 24, 2014\n |accessdate= 2012-08-20\n}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Northwest Athletic Clubs]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://lifetime.life Life Time Website]\n\n{{Minnesota Corporations}}\n\n[[Category:Companies formerly listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Minnesota]]\n[[Category:Health clubs in the United States]]\n[[Category:2015 mergers and acquisitions]]\n[[Category:Private equity portfolio companies]]\n[[Category:Medical and health organizations based in Minnesota]]\n[[Category:Chanhassen, Minnesota]]\n", "name_user": "Rockey45", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200ehttps://https://topshealthinfo.com/lifetime-fitness-membership-prices-locations)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life_Time_Fitness"}
