19\n\n| title10 = [[Freedom (Beyonc\u00e9 song)|Freedom]]\n| note10 = featuring [[Kendrick Lamar]]\n| writer10 = {{flatlist|\n* Beyonc\u00e9\n* [[Jonny Coffer|Jonathan Coffer]]\n* [[Carla Marie Williams|Carla Williams]]\n* [[Arrow Benjamin]]\n* [[Kendrick Lamar|Kendrick Duckworth]]\n* Frank Tirado\n* [[Alan Lomax]]\n* [[John Lomax, Sr.]]}}\n| extra10 = {{hlist|Beyonc\u00e9{{ref|a|[a]}}|Coffer|[[Just Blaze]]}}\n| length10 = 4:49\n\n| title11 = [[All Night (Beyonc\u00e9 song)|All Night]]\n| writer11 = {{flatlist|\n* Beyonc\u00e9\n* Pentz\n* [[King Henry (producer)|Henry Allen]]\n* [[Rock City (duo)|Timothy Thomas]]\n* [[Rock City (duo)|Theron Thomas]]\n* Ilsey Juber\n* Akil King\n* Jaramye Daniels\n* [[Andr\u00e9 Benjamin]]\n* [[Sleepy Brown|Patrick Brown]]\n* [[Big Boi|Antwan Patton]]}}\n| extra11 = {{hlist|Beyonc\u00e9{{ref|a|[a]}}|Diplo|[[King Henry (producer)|King Henry]]}}\n| length11 = 5:21\n\n| title12 = [[Formation (song)|Formation]]\n| length12 = 3:26\n| writer12 = {{hlist|Beyonc\u00e9|[[Mike Will Made It|Michael L. Williams II]]|[[Swae Lee|Khalif Brown]]|[[EarDrummers Entertainment#In-house producers|Asheton Hogan]]}}\n| extra12 = {{hlist|Beyonc\u00e9{{ref|a|[a]}}|[[Mike Will Made It|Mike Will Made-It]]|[[EarDrummers Entertainment#In-house producers|Pluss]]{{ref|b|[b]}}}}}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Lemonade'' {{nobold|\u2013 Streaming edition (bonus track)}}\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| title_width = 30%\n| writing_width = 40%\n| extra_width = 30%\n| total_length = 49:06\n\n| title13 = [[Sorry (Beyonc\u00e9 song)|Sorry]]\n| note13 = original demo\n| writer13 = {{hlist|Beyonc\u00e9|Gordon|Daniel Jones}}\n| extra13 = {{hlist|Beyonc\u00e9|D. Jones}}\n| length13 = 3:24}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Lemonade'' {{nobold|\u2013 Disc two (Visual)}}\n| extra_column = Director(s)\n| title_width = 30%\n| extra_width = 70%\n\n| title1 = Lemonade\n| length1 = 65:22\n| extra1 = {{flatlist|\n* Beyonc\u00e9 Knowles-Carter\n* [[Kahlil Joseph (filmmaker)|Kahlil Joseph]]\n* [[Melina Matsoukas]]{{ref|d|[d]}}\n* Todd Tourso{{ref|d|[d]}}\n* Dikayl Rimmasch{{ref|d|[d]}}\n* [[Jonas \u00c5kerlund]]{{ref|d|[d]}}\n* [[Mark Romanek]]{{ref|d|[d]}}\n}}}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n* All songs are stylised in caps, according to the album's release on Tidal.\n* <sup>{{note|a|[a]}}</sup> signifies a [[Record producer|producer]] and vocal producer.\n* <sup>{{note|b|[b]}}</sup> signifies a co-producer.\n* <sup>{{note|c|[c]}}</sup> signifies an additional producer.\n* <sup>{{note|d|[d]}}</sup> signifies an additional [[Film director|director]].\n* <sup>{{note|e|[e]}}</sup> [[Mort Shuman]] is incorrectly credited as Mort Schuman.\n* \"Hold Up\" features background vocals by [[MeLo-X]].\n* \"Don't Hurt Yourself\" features background vocals by [[Ruby Amanfu]].\n* \"Sorry\" features background vocals by Chrissy Collins.\n* \"6 Inch\" features additional vocals by [[Belly (rapper)|Belly]].\n* \"Freedom\" features background vocals by Arrow Benjamin.\n* \"All Night\" features background vocals by [[Diplo]] and King Henry.\n\n'''Sample credits'''<ref name=\"Album booklet\" />\n* \"Hold Up\"\n** contains elements of \"[[Can't Get Used to Losing You]]\", performed by [[Andy Williams]], written by [[Doc Pomus]] and [[Mort Shuman]].\n** embodies portions of \"[[Turn My Swag On]]\", performed by [[Soulja Boy]], written by [[Soulja Boy|DeAndre Way]], Antonio Randolph and Kelvin McConnell.\n** contains elements of \"[[Maps (Yeah Yeah Yeahs song)|Maps]]\", performed by the [[Yeah Yeah Yeahs]], written by [[Brian Chase]], [[Karen Orzolek]] and [[Nick Zinner]].\n\n* \"Don't Hurt Yourself\"\n** features samples from \"[[When the Levee Breaks#Led Zeppelin version|When the Levee Breaks]]\", performed by [[Led Zeppelin]], written by [[Jimmy Page|James Page]], [[Robert Plant]], [[John Paul Jones (musician)|John Paul Jones]] and [[John Bonham]].\n\n* \"6 Inch\"\n** embodies portions of \"[[My Girls (Animal Collective song)|My Girls]]\", performed by [[Animal Collective]], written by [[Avey Tare|Dave Portner]], [[Panda Bear (musician)|Noah Lennox]] and [[Geologist (musician)|Brian Weitz]].\n** contains samples from \"[[Walk On By (song)|Walk On By]]\", performed by [[Isaac Hayes]], written by [[Burt Bacharach]] and [[Hal David]].\n\n* \"Freedom\"\n** contains a sample of \"Let Me Try\", performed by Kaleidoscope, written by Frank Tirado.\n** contains a sample of \"Collection Speech/Unidentified Lining Hymn\", performed by Reverend R.C. Crenshaw, recorded by [[Alan Lomax]].\n** contains a sample of \"Stewball\", performed by Prisoner \"22\" at [[Mississippi State Penitentiary|Mississippi State Penitentiary at Parchman]], recorded by Alan Lomax and [[John Lomax|John Lomax, Sr.]]\n\n* \"All Night\"\n** contains elements of \"[[Aquemini|SpottieOttieDopaliscious]]\", performed by [[OutKast]], written by [[Andr\u00e9 Benjamin]], [[Antwan Patton]] and [[Sleepy Brown|Patrick Brown]].\n\n*\"Sorry (original demo)\"\n** interpolates \"[[Young, Wild & Free]]\", as performed by [[Snoop Dogg]], [[Wiz Khalifa]] and [[Bruno Mars]].\n\n* ''Lemonade''\n** contains a sample of \"[[The Court of the Crimson King]]\", performed by [[King Crimson]], written by [[Ian McDonald (musician)|Ian McDonald]] and [[Peter Sinfield]].\n\n== Personnel ==\nCredits from Beyonc\u00e9's official website.<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728140451/http://www.beyonce.com/album/lemonade-visual-album/?media_view=credits|archive-date=July 28, 2017|url=http://www.beyonce.com/album/lemonade-visual-album/?media_view=credits|title=Lemonade Credits|work=Beyonce.com}}</ref>\n;Musicians\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n*Beyonc\u00e9 \u2013 vocals\n* [[Eric Gorfain]] \u2013 orchestrations {{small|(tracks 1, 3, 11)}}\n* [[Jon Brion]] - string arrangements {{small|(tracks 1, 3, 11)}}\n* String section {{small|(tracks 1, 3, 11)}}\n** Eric Gorfain and Crystal Alforque, Briana Bandy, Charlie Bisharat, Denise Briese, [[Anna Bulbrook]], Susan Chatman, Daphne Chen, 